{"lemma":"عِنانٌ","slug":"عِنانٌ","root":"ع.ن.ن","root_slug":"ع-ن-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ن-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30655","n30656","n32494"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clouds, stratosphere, cloudy sky","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a bridle strap attached to a horse headstall, a rein","tags":["countable"],"examples":[{"text":"قَالَ حَسَّانُ\nهَجَوْتَ مُحَمَّدًا فَأَجَبْتُ عَنْهُ وَعِنْدَ اللَّهِ فِي ذَاكَ الْجَزَاءُ\nهَجَوْتَ مُحَمَّدًا بَرًّا تَقِيًّا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ شِيمَتُهُ الْوَفَاءُ\nفَإِنَّ أَبِي وَوَالِدَهُ وَعِرْضِي لِعِرْضِ مُحَمَّدٍ مِنْكُمْ وِقَاءُ\nثَكِلْتُ بُنَيَّتِي إِنْ لَمْ تَرَوْهَا تُثِيرُ النَّقْعَ مِنْ كَنَفَيْ كَدَاءِ\nيُبَارِينَ الأَعِنَّةَ مُصْعِدَاتٍ عَلَى أَكْتَافِهَا الأَسَلُ الظِّمَاءُ\nتَظَلُّ جِيَادُنَا مُتَمَطِّرَاتٍ تُلَطِّمُهُنَّ بِالْخُمُرِ النِّسَاءُ","english":"Thus said Hassān,\n\"You railed against Muḥammad. I struck back for him. With God, and God alone, is my reward:\nYou railed against the dutiful and pious—him, the Prophet, whose great mark is faithfulness.\nMy father and my father's father and my name, they are, for him, a shield from you!\nSo may I lose my little one if you do not see them kicking up dust about Kadāʾ!\nOutracing straps and reins, charging onward, on their backs are thirsting spearheads and tips and blades!\nOur troops—they shall stream through, and your women with their scarves and veils shall scuttle to flap them back!"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Aramaic עֲנָנָא (ʿănānā) and Hebrew עָנָן (anán, “cloud”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30655","headword_ar":"عَنَانٌ","root":"En","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clouds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clouds appearing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"presenting themselves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending sideways, in the horizon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbN EaAn~N","text_ar":"سَحَابٌ عَانٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as retain the water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) one whereof is termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanaAnapN","text_ar":"عَنَانَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAn~apN","text_ar":"عَانَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanaAnu Als~amaA='i","text_ar":"عَنَانُ السَّمَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, MF, TA,) in the K said to be ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinaAn","text_ar":"عِنَان","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, but the former is the right, (MF, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lofty region of the sky:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what appears, of the sky, to one looking at it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonaAnN","text_ar":"اَعْنَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanaAnu Ald~aAri","text_ar":"عَنَانُ الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", likewise with fet-h, accord. to the K ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinaAn","text_ar":"عِنَان","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, which is wrong, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The side of the house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that appears to one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","Mgh","MF"]},{"entry_id":"n30656","headword_ar":"عِنَانٌ","root":"En","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EananN","text_ar":"عَنَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b2-  Also an inf. n. of 3 [q. v.]. (TA.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain appertenance of a horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;) [i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rein;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strap of the bridle, by means of which the horse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"similar beast, is withheld:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [said to be] so called because it lies over against the mouth, not entering into it, (Msb,) or because its two straps lie over against the two sides of the neck of the beast, on the right and left: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEin~apN","text_ar":"اَعِنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EununN","text_ar":"عُنُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or, accord. to Sb, the former only. (TA.) [Sometimes it may be rendered The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bridle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the first of the following phrases.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vanayotu EalaY Alfarasi","text_ar":"ثَنَيْتُ عَلَى الفَرَسِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinaAnahu","text_ar":"عِنَانَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I put upon the horse his bridle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasN","text_ar":"فَرَسٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSiyru AlEinaAni","text_ar":"قَصِيرُ العِنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse short in the rein"},{"kind":"text","text":"] implies discommendation, as denoting shortness of the neck: [but]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa qaSiyru AlEinaAni","text_ar":"هُوَ قَصِيرُ العِنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[said of a man] means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qliylu Alxayori","text_ar":"قلِيلُ الخَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is one possessing little,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no, good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"few,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no, good things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"little,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no, goodness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laTawiylu AlEinaAni","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَطَوِيلُ العِنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is one whose rein is long"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an exalted person; of great chiefdom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN Tarifu AlEinaAni","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ طَرِفُ العِنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K, TA, TK, in one of my copies of the S"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tarfu","text_ar":"طَرفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in the other"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Trafu","text_ar":"طرَفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taroqu","text_ar":"طَرْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [but correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tarif","text_ar":"طَرِف"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"katif","text_ar":"كَتِف"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is said in the TK,]) means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abiY~u AlEinaAni","text_ar":"اَبِىُّ العِنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is one who refuses the rein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw AlEinaAni","text_ar":"ذُو العِنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to the horse means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tractable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*al~a EinaAnu","text_ar":"ذَلَّ عِنَانُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one became submissive."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abog","text_ar":"ابْغ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino EinaAnihi","text_ar":"مِنْ عِنَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in which the first word is written in my original thus, but it has been altered by the copyist, and I doubt not that it is correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroxi","text_ar":"اَرْخِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the phrase, reading thus, being well known, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Slacken thou his rein,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ease thou him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relieve him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aivoni EalaY~a EinaAnahu","text_ar":"اِثْنِ عَلَىَّ عِنَانَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Turn thou back"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bend thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards me his rein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA=' vaAniyFA fiY EinaAnihi","text_ar":"جَا=ء ثَانِيًا فِى عِنَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thus in my original, but correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino EnAnh","text_ar":"مِنْ عنانه"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vnY","text_ar":"ثنى"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came bending"},{"kind":"text","text":"a part"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his rein,"},{"kind":"text","text":"turning from his course,] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came having"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accomplished the object of his want."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaA^a EinaAna","text_ar":"مَلَاَ عِنَانَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAb~atihi","text_ar":"دَابَّتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"urged, his beast to run vehemently."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And [hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimotalaA^a EinaAnuhu","text_ar":"اِمْتَلَاَ عِنَانُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The utmost of his power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability, was accomplished."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA yajoriyaAni fiY EinaAnK","text_ar":"هُمَا يَجْرِيَانِ فِى عِنَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They two are equal"},{"kind":"text","text":"in excellence or otherwise. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A heat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"single run to a goal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraY Alfarasu EinaAnFA","text_ar":"جَرَى الفَرَسُ عِنَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The horse ran a heat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabaA fiY EinaAnihi","text_ar":"كَبَا فِى عِنَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stumbled in his heat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See also an ex., in a verse of Et- Tirimmáh, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the middle of the paragraph. And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EananN","text_ar":"عَنَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A heat"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a beast: and also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beginning of speech:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence the prov.,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"muEotariDN liEananK lamo yaEonihi"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Addressing himself to that which is not of his business"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA layosa mino $aA^onihi","text_ar":"مَا لَيْسَ مِنْ شَاْنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (Meyd.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A long rope"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cord."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEinaAnu","text_ar":"العِنَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habolu Almatoni","text_ar":"حَبْلُ المَتْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cord of the portion of the back along which extends the spine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the spinal cord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"medulla spinalis,"},{"kind":"text","text":"considered as a single cord]: (K:) [but this consists of two lateral cords, connected together: and therefore, app., it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinaAnaA","text_ar":"عِنَانَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almatoni","text_ar":"المَتْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabolaAhu","text_ar":"حَبْلَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two cords of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maton","text_ar":"مَتْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$irokapu AlEinaAni","text_ar":"شِرْكَةُ العِنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The copartnership of two persons in one particular thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exclusive of the rest of the articles of property of either:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, * K:) as though a thing presented itself to them ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~a lahumaA","text_ar":"عَنَّ لَهُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, Mgh, Msb) and they bought it (S) and they then became copartners in it: (S, Mgh, Msb:) so says ISk: (Mgh:) or it is from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinaAn","text_ar":"عِنَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the horse, because each assigns to his companion the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EnAn","text_ar":"عنان"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the free management of part of the property: (Mgh, Msb:) or because it is allowable for them to differ, like as does the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EnAn","text_ar":"عنان"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the hand of the rider when pulled and when slackened: (Mgh:) or, accord. to Az, it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the case in which each of the two copartners produces deenárs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dirhems, which they mix together, and each gives permission to the other to traffic therewith:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the lawyers differ not in respect of its being lawful; if they gain upon the two sums, the gain being between them; and if they lose, the loss being on the head of each of them [equally]: the partnership of two persons in everything that is in their possession is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$irokapu AlmufaAwaDapi","text_ar":"شِرْكَةُ المُفَاوَضَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (TA:) or it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the case of one's competing with a man in the making of a purchase, and saying to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"“"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Make me to be a partner with thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"”"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this being before he"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the purchaser]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"becomes entitled to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algalaq","text_ar":"الغَلَق"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algiloq","text_ar":"الغِلْق"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlElq","text_ar":"العلق"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEalaq","text_ar":"العَلَق"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K: [the last word in this explanation, thus written in four different ways in different copies of the K, following the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabola A^ano yasotawojiba","text_ar":"قَبْلَ اَنْ يَسْتَوْجِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", I think to be most probably"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algalaqa","text_ar":"الغَلَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"irredeemability"},{"kind":"text","text":"by the seller, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiqa Alr~ahonu","text_ar":"غَلِقَ الرَّهْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the case of two persons' being equal in partnership,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of what they contribute of gold"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silver;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinaAn","text_ar":"عِنَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the beast; (TA;) because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EnAn","text_ar":"عنان"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the beast consists of two equal single pieces: (Z, Msb, K, TA:) or it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEinaAn","text_ar":"العِنَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuEaAn~ap","text_ar":"المُعَانَّة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuEaAraDap","text_ar":"المُعَارَضَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, TA;) because each of them does like as does the other in respect of his property [that he supplies] and in selling and buying. (TA.) See an ex. in a verse cited in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$rk","text_ar":"شرك"},{"kind":"text","text":", conj. 3. ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanaAnN","text_ar":"عَنَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["K","Msb","TA","S","Mgh","Z"]},{"entry_id":"n32494","headword_ar":"عُنَانٌ","root":"gn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, near the end."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}